And I think because it just sensitizes
our receptors here, more or less,

00:29:43.650 --> 00:29:48.190
and gets them kind of
excited about enjoying food.

00:29:48.190 --> 00:29:56.050
So al dente for an Italian is
imperative for pasta and risotto.

00:29:56.050 --> 00:30:01.450
So I'm looking-- it's being tested.

00:30:01.450 --> 00:30:03.900
It's toasting slowly.

00:30:03.900 --> 00:30:14.390
So I said that rice has 95% starch,
and it's not tasty, as it is.

00:30:14.390 --> 00:30:17.010
It's starchy, as a matter of fact.

00:30:17.010 --> 00:30:19.560
So you have to kind of season it.

00:30:19.560 --> 00:30:25.460
So at this point where it's nice
and dry and when it's thirsty,

00:30:25.460 --> 00:30:27.710
you put white wine.

00:30:27.710 --> 00:30:30.490
And wine.

00:30:30.490 --> 00:30:32.300
I always get, what kind of wine?

00:30:32.300 --> 00:30:32.840
A good wine.

00:30:32.840 --> 00:30:34.250
A wine that you would drink.

00:30:34.250 --> 00:30:36.650
A wine that you have some left over.

00:30:36.650 --> 00:30:37.830
Just don't do cooking wine.

00:30:37.830 --> 00:30:41.990
Cooking wine has all kinds of
seasoning and salts and all kinds.

00:30:41.990 --> 00:30:43.982
And at this point, nice and dry.

00:30:43.982 --> 00:30:45.830
[SIZZLE]

00:30:45.830 --> 00:30:49.280
You'll hear that-- that siz.

00:30:49.280 --> 00:30:54.330
And what's happening is that
the rice is taking it in.

00:30:54.330 --> 00:30:59.120
So when you're cooking with
wine, you want the acidity.

00:30:59.120 --> 00:31:00.800
You want the flavor.

00:31:00.800 --> 00:31:04.130
The alcohol dissipates
in 10, 15 minutes.

00:31:04.130 --> 00:31:11.930
The alcohol will have dissipated and
the rice will be balanced on the inside.

00:31:11.930 --> 00:31:14.930
So when you eat that
rice, it has flavor.

00:31:14.930 --> 00:31:17.630
It has the acidity, and it has
some of the flavor of wine.

00:31:17.630 --> 00:31:21.990
And then it will take on the
flavor of everything else.

00:31:21.990 --> 00:31:29.170
But at this point, I want to bring
the rice again down completely

00:31:29.170 --> 00:31:34.085
to a dry level before I add the stock.

00:31:42.353 --> 00:31:42.853
OK.

