at the same-- given the same time.

00:34:22.250 --> 00:34:26.230
So I'm always trying to get everything
in there, cooking at the same time.

00:34:26.230 --> 00:34:32.380
Just enough liquid to kind of-- when
you press like this, you see the bottom,

00:34:32.380 --> 00:34:33.969
but not that much.

00:34:33.969 --> 00:34:43.340
And again, you know, if you're
doing in chemistry or whatever,

00:34:43.340 --> 00:34:46.790
you put ingredients
together in a liquid.

00:34:46.790 --> 00:34:48.800
They'll try to neutralize each other.

00:34:48.800 --> 00:34:51.320
Pull everything out
of one so it combines.

00:34:51.320 --> 00:34:53.389
And this happens here as well.

00:34:53.389 --> 00:34:54.080
You say, OK.

00:34:54.080 --> 00:34:56.504
You're going to stay there
18 minutes and going to stir.

00:34:56.504 --> 00:34:57.920
Just-- you know how much it takes.

00:34:57.920 --> 00:35:01.370
Put all that liquid in there,
and go and do your chores.

00:35:01.370 --> 00:35:03.260
But it doesn't happen,
because the technique,

00:35:03.260 --> 00:35:06.890
