do you cook your risotto?

00:41:17.010 --> 00:41:18.990
Certainly not at maximum.

00:41:18.990 --> 00:41:23.700
You cook it so that everything
continues, that this reaction that's

00:41:23.700 --> 00:41:26.640
happening continues at the same speed.

00:41:26.640 --> 00:41:32.520
That as you can see, that the stock
evaporates, the flavor of the stock

00:41:32.520 --> 00:41:33.660
remains there.

00:41:33.660 --> 00:41:37.860
But at the same time, it
pulls out the starches.

00:41:37.860 --> 00:41:39.450
And so it continues.

