00:44:31.320 --> 00:44:35.250
When you use rice--

00:44:35.250 --> 00:44:39.850
and because rice has
certainly many uses.

00:44:39.850 --> 00:44:45.760
We use it in Italy a lot for
soups, especially vegetable soups

00:44:45.760 --> 00:44:46.600
just as that extra.

00:44:46.600 --> 00:44:52.630
We use also pasta, tubettini
or whatever we put in the soup.

00:44:52.630 --> 00:44:57.910
But rice, if you do use it for
your soup, as well as pasta,

00:44:57.910 --> 00:44:59.210
you boil it in the soup.

00:44:59.210 --> 00:45:03.160
You don't make a whole pot of soup,
put the rice, and then put it away.

00:45:03.160 --> 00:45:05.380
And then you pull and you reheat it.

00:45:05.380 --> 00:45:11.230
The rice and the pasta should be
cooked in that soup before serving.

00:45:11.230 --> 00:45:12.370
It should not be--

00:45:12.370 --> 00:45:16.720
the one option that you have
is that you cook the rice maybe

00:45:16.720 --> 00:45:21.230
separately in water and even pasta,
and you leave it on the side.

00:45:21.230 --> 00:45:26.140
And then when your guest comes,
you leave it a little bit al dente.

00:45:26.140 --> 00:45:29.710
You just add it the last
minute, and then you serve it.

