then it's a beautiful
thing to do, because you

00:46:11.200 --> 00:46:13.150
can converse like I do with you.

00:46:13.150 --> 00:46:16.210
You can have some of the
kids mixing it or whatever.

00:46:16.210 --> 00:46:17.860
And you know, the aromas.

00:46:17.860 --> 00:46:19.810
And you look like a great chef.

00:46:19.810 --> 00:46:23.440
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:23.440 --> 00:46:27.892
But if you want to prepare some,
certainly the mise en place,

00:46:27.892 --> 00:46:30.850
as we call it in our industry, the
preparation and everything, cutting,

00:46:30.850 --> 00:46:33.250
everything, that's permissible.

00:46:33.250 --> 00:46:37.600
The only part of the risotto
that you can do ahead

00:46:37.600 --> 00:46:46.300
is that you toast them and you
add the wine and you dry it back,

00:46:46.300 --> 00:46:48.820
and then you spread it and you leave it.

00:46:48.820 --> 00:46:52.390
But still, you know, it loses
something, because then it's cold.

00:46:52.390 --> 00:46:55.690
It has congealed to some
extent, the starches.

00:46:55.690 --> 00:46:59.800
And then you have to bring it
back to life, bring it back to--

00:46:59.800 --> 00:47:01.780
so I think if you're seeing--

00:47:01.780 --> 00:47:06.250
do you see how the liquid is getting--

00:47:06.250 --> 00:47:07.510
is there too much light?

00:47:07.510 --> 00:47:13.630
Can you see the creaminess of the rice?

00:47:19.890 --> 00:47:24.460
Risotto, the one thing that's good
about the risotto is that, you know,

00:47:24.460 --> 00:47:31.270
you can make one pot, and it would
feed a substantial amount of people.

00:47:31.270 --> 00:47:35.110
But you have to serve it
as soon as you make it.

00:47:35.110 --> 00:47:42.250
And you know, risotto, as well as pasta,
you know, one is concerned evermore,

00:47:42.250 --> 00:47:43.450
you know, of starches.

00:47:43.450 --> 00:47:46.000
So much starches today, everybody.

00:47:46.000 --> 00:47:51.556
You just kind of change the ratio
of your vegetables, your proteins,

00:47:51.556 --> 00:47:52.180
and your pasta.

00:47:52.180 --> 00:47:56.440
And instead of having
80% pasta, 20% vegetable,

00:47:56.440 --> 00:48:01.370
you can have one third vegetable, one
third proteins, and one third pasta.

00:48:01.370 --> 00:48:03.260
Who says you can't?

00:48:03.260 --> 00:48:05.660
You can get the satisfaction
and the pleasure,

00:48:05.660 --> 00:48:07.490
and you're balancing your meal.

00:48:07.490 --> 00:48:10.130
And you can do the same with risotto.

00:48:10.130 --> 00:48:16.375
Add more vegetables and proteins.

00:48:19.090 --> 00:48:21.390
The last step in--

00:48:26.250 --> 00:48:28.194
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:28.194 --> 00:48:29.120
Coming along.

