[LAUGHTER]

00:57:10.600 --> 00:57:19.070
So the last step in a
risotto is the mantecare.

00:57:19.070 --> 00:57:21.330
Mantecare is sort of the whip.

00:57:21.330 --> 00:57:27.420
And you do that--

00:57:27.420 --> 00:57:28.500
some great cheese.

00:57:28.500 --> 00:57:29.790
Grana Padano cheese.

00:57:29.790 --> 00:57:31.350
I love that cheese there.

00:57:31.350 --> 00:57:33.940
100% cow's milk cheese.

00:57:33.940 --> 00:57:37.560
It's in the Emilia-Romanga in Lombardy.

00:57:37.560 --> 00:57:41.770
And cubes of butter at room temperature.

00:57:41.770 --> 00:57:47.850
So when you have products like
this like butter or cheese,

00:57:47.850 --> 00:57:51.420
these are products that
are almost finished.

00:57:51.420 --> 00:57:55.350
And the more you cook them,
the more you lose their flavor.

00:57:55.350 --> 00:57:58.680
If you cook with butter from the
beginning-- had I put all this,

00:57:58.680 --> 00:58:00.120
it would have separated.

00:58:00.120 --> 00:58:02.040
I would have gotten all the fat.

00:58:02.040 --> 00:58:05.400
The flavonoids, the nice
aroma would have dissipated,

00:58:05.400 --> 00:58:10.090
and I would have gotten maybe half of
the value in flavor of that butter.

00:58:10.090 --> 00:58:14.100
So if you love butter, but you
don't want to use it that much,

00:58:14.100 --> 00:58:15.750
add it at the end.

00:58:15.750 --> 00:58:18.030
At the end, the last
moment, just let it--

00:58:18.030 --> 00:58:21.880
you'll get the maximum of the flavors,
the flavonoids, and everything,

00:58:21.880 --> 00:58:23.670
and it will not separate.

00:58:23.670 --> 00:58:28.480
Cheese is sort of a
pre-digested product,

00:58:28.480 --> 00:58:33.270
because you know, the bacteria
of the cheese itself break--

00:58:33.270 --> 00:58:35.370
that's what aging cheese is all about.

00:58:35.370 --> 00:58:42.090
Breaks down the proteins into these
wonderful kind of molecules of cheese

00:58:42.090 --> 00:58:43.530
with all its aroma.

00:58:43.530 --> 00:58:48.820
If you cook it, if you apply heat, you
get the string and the puddles of fat,

00:58:48.820 --> 00:58:54.130
I'm sure when you cook cheese, because
you are breaking it down further.

00:58:54.130 --> 00:58:55.260
So you want it--

00:58:55.260 --> 00:58:57.900
this is maximum for cheese and butter.

00:58:57.900 --> 00:59:05.480
And mantecare is the last step
when you will take it off the fire,

00:59:05.480 --> 00:59:09.230
or just shut the fire, and
whip it in the last minute.

00:59:09.230 --> 00:59:11.270
And you'll get the
maximum, one or the other.

00:59:11.270 --> 00:59:14.630
And then just a little bit of
scallions, just a little greenness

00:59:14.630 --> 00:59:21.657
to freshen up this
complexity of flavors.

