00:59:53.230 --> 01:00:01.380
So risotto, sometimes people
prefer it nice and dense.

01:00:01.380 --> 01:00:07.470
Means only being careful of towards
the end how much liquid you add and let

01:00:07.470 --> 01:00:11.330
evaporate, and the
risotto is nice and dense.

01:00:11.330 --> 01:00:18.390
In Italy, we like it also loose, and
it's called all'onda, to the wave.

01:00:18.390 --> 01:00:21.580
And that's, again, you see
now it's kind of looser.

01:00:21.580 --> 01:00:26.860
It's just a question of gauging
the liquid towards the end,

01:00:26.860 --> 01:00:29.620
but not overcooking it.

01:00:29.620 --> 01:00:36.130
And all'onda risotto usually is
best with lighter-- with seafood,

01:00:36.130 --> 01:00:37.930
with vegetables.

01:00:37.930 --> 01:00:46.210
And then denser risotto is maybe
better with meats and game and so on.

